YOU NEED TO CONSULT THE PROBLEMS THAT EXIST HERE, you should come and take a tour to consult before deciding whether to let your relatives give birth here or not. 1. ATMOSPHERE: The delivery room is located next to the parking lot. Most of the ground floor area is used for parking purposes. In the same motorbike parking area is a system of rooms for normal births and cesarean sections. The atmosphere here is very unpleasant because the dust and smoke from the street seeps in through the parking lot where there are always cars going in and out. While the door into the delivery room is also the door out of the delivery room and the atmosphere here is very bad. If a healthy adult feels very uncomfortable while waiting, what can you say about the air quality inside the delivery room? 2. SANITATION: Currently the hospital is overloaded. Although the cleaning staff have made great efforts, the number is still very small compared to the number of people giving birth. It is necessary to strengthen the cleaning staff to be proportionate and appropriate. 3. SMELL: The bathroom structure is located in the nursing room, but the bathroom exhaust fan has been disabled, making the whole room very smelly. If this exhaust fan operates, the amount of outside air coming in will be the stinging air from the parking lot on the ground floor that rushes into the rooms on the upper floors due to the skylight design connecting directly from the parking area. As long as the ground floor is still used to park cars, this problem will still exist even if there is a restriction on starting the car engine when entering and exiting the parking area. Or solve it by opening the outside ventilation windows for each room and taking care of the bathroom exhaust system more often. Need to pay more attention to hygiene in the nursing room. 4. POST-BIRTH CARE: Cleaning for women after giving birth every day is very necessary, but most women do not dare to use this service a second time because it is very painful. Most family members help women clean every day even though they still have to pay for this service. 5. NOISE: The issue of visitation is not strictly enforced, allowing many relatives to bring children to stay with them, it is like a kindergarten for all ages so it is extremely noisy. Very sorry for the babies and mothers. If the hospital is comfortable with visits, it is necessary to arrange a place to rest for visitors. Currently, there are a lot of family members going to feed the children, making terrible noise with the children, carpets lying on the floor all over the place, not to mention food and garbage. This issue needs regular attention and monitoring. In particular, the problem of sound pollution is extremely serious. 6. COST: The advance for a normal birth here is currently 11 million VND, the price is not commensurate with the quality of service. Just like other places that emerged for a while and then became overloaded, here the quality of all postpartum services is deteriorating. The number of people coming to give birth is almost always overloaded. - I am someone who has used the services here and visited many other births, so I want to give my opinion to those who will be customers of the hospital as well as to the hospital's leadership.
